1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:29,200
 Fajlj,Išu si Marija,lijep pozdrav svim gledatelima koji nas danas gledaju,drago mi što vas mogu pozdraviti,ja sam Mersi Bilanđija,a današnji post našeg intervjua za našeg kanalu je doktor Dave de la Cruz,vice-postulator,Gauze za protišenje svetim Blaženeg Ivana Mersa.Posebnost ovog intervjua je to što je naš gos Filipina,i što

2
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:38,280
 jednog Hrvatskog svijeta,a promovirama Filipinima na jedan posebno način,a više o tome slučite ovog intervju.

3
00:00:38,280 --> 00:00:45,840
 Doktor Dave,drago mi za biti ovdje što je tu s nami,drago mi za izgledati svoje zbavljenje za nami.

4
00:00:45,840 --> 00:00:51,660
 I specialno dvijek za Padre Božidara koji te povrlo u Krojačiji.

5
00:00:51,660 --> 00:01:11,380
 Hrvatskog svijeta,a kako se povrlo u Vrstu,a kako se povrlo u Vrstu,a kako se povrlo u Vrstu,a kako se povrlo u Vrstu?

6
00:01:11,380 --> 00:01:13,380
 Hrvatskog svijeta,a kako se povrlo u Vrstu,a kako se povrlo u Vrstu,a kako se povrlo u Hrvatskog svijeta.

7
00:01:13,380 --> 00:01:35,380
 Dr. Dave Delacruz,a kako se povrlo u Vrstu,a kako se povrlo u Vrstu.a kako se povrlo u Vrstu.a kako se povrlo u Vrstu.a kako se povrlo u Vrstu.a kako se povrlo u Vrstu.a kako se povrlo u Vrstu.a kako se povrlo u Vrstu.a kako se povrlo.

8
00:01:35,380 --> 00:01:44,040
 I came from the Philippines, a 500-year-old Christian country, which we celebrated just two years ago.

9
00:01:44,040 --> 00:01:52,900
 And our country is known as the largest Catholic country in Asia and the third in the world.

10
00:01:52,900 --> 00:01:56,900
 So we have 85 million Catholics in the Philippines.

11
00:01:57,340 --> 00:02:06,240
 And the Philippines is very interesting because amidst of our different cultures and our different ethnic groups,

12
00:02:06,240 --> 00:02:17,020
 the Catholic faith becomes the sign of unity for our nation from the very famous bloodless revolution

13
00:02:17,020 --> 00:02:25,800
 that brought us Corazon Aquino as our first woman president until the second Edsa revolution, as what we call it.

14
00:02:25,800 --> 00:02:36,420
 And until now, the Catholic faith stands, you know, as a sign of peace and unity for the Filipino Catholics.

15
00:02:36,420 --> 00:02:40,960
 Wow, that's great. So third largest Catholic in the world.

16
00:02:40,960 --> 00:02:46,980
 Wow, that's beautiful. And how did Catholicism came to the Philippines?

17
00:02:46,980 --> 00:03:00,720
 Yeah, in 1521, 502 years ago, when the famous Magellan, Ferdinand Magellan, the one who was very famous in his circumnavigation of the world,

18
00:03:00,720 --> 00:03:09,600
 came into our archipelago and brought the Catholicism, of course, the Spanish crown with him,

19
00:03:09,600 --> 00:03:12,300
 and the desire of expanding the colony of Spain.

20
00:03:12,300 --> 00:03:26,640
 And from that point, he has given us this wonderful gift of the Catholic faith by giving us the first baptism of our ancestors.

21
00:03:26,640 --> 00:03:35,480
 And then here comes the famous image statue of the Holy Child Jesus, as we call it, Santo Nino.

22
00:03:35,480 --> 00:03:46,920
 And then from there, after he died, still, it was continued by two other famous explorers like Ruy Lopez de Villalobos

23
00:03:46,920 --> 00:03:55,020
 and Miguel Lopez de Legazpi, who really started our nation under the Spanish regime.

24
00:03:55,020 --> 00:04:10,380
 And this country that is very young, if you will see, because we're only 500 years, has already been a gift to the whole world,

25
00:04:10,380 --> 00:04:17,160
 especially in terms of Catholic families, Catholic migrants and immigrants.

26
00:04:17,160 --> 00:04:26,660
 I'm sure here in Croatia, we're having Filipinos, one joke that we always say is that you just drop a water and we will multiply.

27
00:04:26,660 --> 00:04:44,940
 And amidst of this, our immigration and migration crisis in the country, still we see it as a positive sign that Filipinos are really sent to be missionaries,

28
00:04:44,940 --> 00:04:52,120
 Catholic missionaries in their simple prayer life, in their simple Christian values.

29
00:04:52,120 --> 00:05:05,960
 We are very thankful to the Spanish colonizers for giving us this wonderful faith that was developed through spiritual and cultural contextualization.

30
00:05:05,960 --> 00:05:07,900
 Yes, that's beautiful.

31
00:05:07,900 --> 00:05:15,680
 And I just remembered while you were talking about Filipinos coming to Europe and bringing Christian values,

32
00:05:15,680 --> 00:05:29,020
 I heard about the only place in Berlin, Germany, that has 24-hour adoration to the Blessed Sacrament is in Filipino parish.

33
00:05:29,020 --> 00:05:30,020
 Exactly.

34
00:05:30,020 --> 00:05:34,760
 So you are bringing Catalystism back where you received it from.

35
00:05:34,760 --> 00:05:35,960
 That's right, that's right.

36
00:05:35,960 --> 00:05:42,440
 Even I was surprised that here in the Basilica of the Sacred Heart in Zagreb, in the English Mass every Sunday,

37
00:05:42,440 --> 00:05:45,780
 it's the Filipinos who really filled the church.

38
00:05:45,780 --> 00:05:55,780
 And that is wonderful sign that the Catholic faith was really planted well in every Filipinos,

39
00:05:55,780 --> 00:06:00,260
 who are maybe in the Philippines or outside the Philippines.

40
00:06:00,260 --> 00:06:04,560
 And how was that Catholic faith planted in you?

41
00:06:04,560 --> 00:06:09,900
 And how did you come to such a deep devotion to Catholic faith?

42
00:06:09,900 --> 00:06:10,900
 Yeah.

43
00:06:10,900 --> 00:06:19,900
 Normally, as what I heard from many stories, it will always be their mother who will teach them their first prayers,

44
00:06:19,900 --> 00:06:22,780
 their first, you know, Catholic practices.

45
00:06:22,780 --> 00:06:24,320
 Mine is very different.

46
00:06:24,320 --> 00:06:35,660
 And it was my father who taught me my first prayers, who really assist me in my, you know, younger years as altar server in our parish church.

47
00:06:35,660 --> 00:06:40,660
 And then my mom is also very supportive in my mission, even until now.

48
00:06:40,660 --> 00:06:45,200
 Even I'm still already working and I'm already, you know, at this age, no.

49
00:06:45,200 --> 00:06:50,540
 And my parents are, I can say, they are my first teachers of Catholic faith.

50
00:06:50,540 --> 00:06:55,540
 And at the same time, they are the one who nourishes my Catholic faith.

51
00:06:55,540 --> 00:07:04,880
 And, of course, here comes the Blessed Ivan Mers family, Blessed Ivan Mers also has developed that Catholic faith in me.

52
00:07:04,880 --> 00:07:05,880
 Yeah.

53
00:07:05,880 --> 00:07:15,420
 And just before you met Blessed Ivan, you just told me that you had experience with charismatic groups that are in Filipinos.

54
00:07:15,420 --> 00:07:16,460
 Can you share a bit more?

55
00:07:16,460 --> 00:07:17,460
 Yeah, yeah.

56
00:07:17,460 --> 00:07:25,540
 There was a point in my life that I almost wanted to go out of the Catholic church because, you know, there are some politics within the Catholic church.

57
00:07:25,540 --> 00:07:33,120
 But here comes the light of Jesus community that helped me during that crisis of my life.

58
00:07:33,120 --> 00:07:39,620
 So, I was already the vice postulator of Blessed Ivan Mers then, but we do not have yet the center.

59
00:07:39,620 --> 00:07:44,320
 So, I go to Mass in this Catholic charismatic community.

60
00:07:44,320 --> 00:07:53,960
 I attended, you know, these wonderful sessions, you know, because they do not only, you know, touch the spiritual but also the human formation.

61
00:07:53,960 --> 00:08:05,540
 So, this light of Jesus community, especially the feast, as we call it, the feast, founded by Brother Bo Sanchez, a lay Catholic charismatic and theologian.

62
00:08:05,540 --> 00:08:14,540
 During these years of my crisis, he helped me to go back again to this Catholic faith and deepen my relationship with Jesus Christ.

63
00:08:14,540 --> 00:08:26,120
 Until, during those times, I was praying that I want to, you know, we want to build a center for Blessed Ivan, and I was really raising my hands, I said, "Lord, please answer my prayer."

64
00:08:26,120 --> 00:08:41,540
 And in 2017, the first center came out in the Philippines, and until now, we are still having this center and chapel of Blessed Ivan Mers, which I believe was an answered prayer through that, you know, charismatic community.

65
00:08:41,540 --> 00:09:01,060
 Yes, that's beautiful. We are also a charismatic community, and we feel that this experience of charisms of Holy Spirit should do just this, to deepen your faith, to deepen your, and renew your catolic spirituality in a new way.

66
00:09:01,060 --> 00:09:07,960
 And, uh, can you share us a story how you came in touch, how you get to know, uh, Blessed Ivan?

67
00:09:07,960 --> 00:09:20,140
 Yeah, uh, it was in 2005, the summer of 2005, I was still a student of liturgy in this, uh, Saint Paul VI Institute of Liturgy in Burkidnon.

68
00:09:20,140 --> 00:09:48,140
 And our director, uh, Father Anscarcio Pungko, who was then the former, uh, rector of the Pontificio Instituto Liturico in Rome, the first Filipino, and we call him the Father Filipino Liturgy, asked us to have this assignment of finding individuals, saints, or personalities that are, uh, has this contributed to the liturgy of our church.

69
00:09:48,140 --> 00:09:56,840
 So, when I went back to my room, because we are, you know, we were, uh, secluded in one monastery for one month or three months, no?

70
00:09:56,840 --> 00:10:06,260
 So, I researched in the internet, and saw, uh, just typed in saints, liturgy, and came out Blessed Ivan.

71
00:10:06,260 --> 00:10:12,840
 So, I was wondering, who is this guy from, you know, from nowhere? I don't know where he came from.

72
00:10:12,840 --> 00:10:19,540
 So, I opened it, he's from Croatia, and the website during that time where it has already the English texts.

73
00:10:19,540 --> 00:10:28,240
 So, I was reading and presented it to Father Anscarcio Pungko. I said, "Yes, yes, yes, yes, you study that, ano, that person, that Ivan Merz, and make an assignment."

74
00:10:28,240 --> 00:10:38,940
 So, I contacted Father Nagy and the postulation got to, you know, this connection until I passed and graduated in this institute.

75
00:10:38,940 --> 00:10:54,940
 So, thanks to Blessed Ivan Merz. So, then, from then, our connection with Father Nagy, the postulation, the postulator, continued until I was invited to come in Croatia, in Zagreb, in 2007. So, that's my first time.

76
00:10:54,940 --> 00:11:09,640
 And, you know, that experience of being with Blessed Ivan, being with Father Nagy, really deepen my love and relationship with this Croatian Blessed.

77
00:11:09,640 --> 00:11:27,640
 Just imagine for 6,000 miles, here comes, you know, Blessed Ivan in my life. I said, "What in the world we can do this?" But I believe that it is providence, you know, until I was a vice, appointed vice postulator in March 19, 2008.

78
00:11:27,640 --> 00:11:36,340
 And from then, I worked in the promotion of Blessed Ivan, promoting his life, promoting his works, promoting his holiness.

79
00:11:36,340 --> 00:11:45,340
 And the Filipinos are very, you know, welcoming. That is one of our values, of our traits. We are very hospitable.

80
00:11:45,340 --> 00:12:00,040
 So, we welcome also, Blessed Ivan, even if no one knows him, or he is not, you know, that famous like the other Blessed, like Carlo Acutis, or Blessed, during the time, Mother Teresa or Saint John.

81
00:12:00,040 --> 00:12:08,740
 But they are surprised that this Blessed Ivan is a lay person. He never entered the seminary. He never became a priest.

82
00:12:08,740 --> 00:12:25,040
 But this ordinary professor has taught so many young people, so many young Croats during that time, so that these young Croatians, these young Croats, will be the one who will build the new Church of Croatia.

83
00:12:25,040 --> 00:12:36,740
 And of course, Blessed Ivan also built this new Church of Croatia in terms of liturgy, in terms of philosophy, literature, art, etc.

84
00:12:36,740 --> 00:12:46,740
 So, it was not that easy because, you know, everybody can promote Blessed Ivan. Everybody can promote a saint, you know?

85
00:12:46,740 --> 00:13:01,440
 So, later, I will share to you how did we work on this promotion, but at least on that story that you will see that this providence, you know, just imagine from Croatia going to the Philippines, who is this guy?

86
00:13:01,440 --> 00:13:15,140
 But we always tell the Filipinos, Blessed Ivan has inspired many young people who also became saints, like Blessed Aloysius Stepinac, Venerable Marius, Servern of God Marius Tankovic.

87
00:13:15,140 --> 00:13:26,140
 Here comes also the saints who are connected, like Saint John Paul II, Mother Teresa of Calcutta, Cardinal Kujaric.

88
00:13:26,140 --> 00:13:33,840
 So, these are, you know, we can say that he is not only an ordinary teacher, he is also a teacher of saints.

89
00:13:33,840 --> 00:13:46,540
 Yes, yes, yes, that's beautiful name, teacher of saints. And he still does that in Croatian youth, and I'm very happy to see that he is doing the same in the Philippines.

90
00:13:46,540 --> 00:13:47,540
 Yes, yes.

91
00:13:47,540 --> 00:14:00,540
 How did you get started with promotion then when you came back from Croatia to the Philippines? What were your first steps? How did you get started with the work of promoting?

92
00:14:00,540 --> 00:14:12,240
 Yeah, it was not easy. Financially, I was not yet working that time, or maybe I'm already starting working because I started working in 2008.

93
00:14:12,240 --> 00:14:19,040
 So, as what I've mentioned before, many can promote, anyone can promote a saint.

94
00:14:19,040 --> 00:14:26,740
 So, what we did was, you know, to start the traditional way of, you know, giving prayer cards, putting images, you know.

95
00:14:26,740 --> 00:14:35,740
 And we said, "Let's have a little bit, you know, put some spices to make this more, you know, creative."

96
00:14:35,740 --> 00:14:47,440
 So, what we did was to bring the relic of Blessed Ivan into different schools, churches, and still there are a small response.

97
00:14:47,440 --> 00:15:08,140
 Until, during the beatification of St. John Paul II, we were partnered with the diocese of Cubao and this famous mall in Quezon City to make an exhibit about St. John Paul II.

98
00:15:08,140 --> 00:15:15,840
 And I said, "Well, we need to take part because it was St. John Paul, or Blessed John Paul at that time, who beatified Blessed Ivan."

99
00:15:15,840 --> 00:15:19,840
 So, it will be, you know, our way of promoting also Blessed Ivan.

100
00:15:19,840 --> 00:15:29,540
 So, here comes the exhibit, we prepared it with the diocese and that mall, and then there we entered the promotion of Blessed Ivan.

101
00:15:29,540 --> 00:15:40,540
 We placed his image, we gave prayer cards, and then, believe it or not, more than 1,000 people come to that exhibit per day.

102
00:15:40,540 --> 00:15:44,840
 And we were there around two weeks, so 14 days.

103
00:15:44,840 --> 00:15:50,040
 So, just imagine that how many people has already getting to know Blessed Ivan.

104
00:15:50,040 --> 00:15:57,540
 And here comes another that Mother Teresa was canonized, St. John Paul was canonized, you know.

105
00:15:57,540 --> 00:16:07,840
 So, we infuse Blessed Ivan with this, you know, famous saints, and at the back of it, we will always say, "It's because of Blessed Ivan."

106
00:16:07,840 --> 00:16:09,840
 We have this, it's because of him.

107
00:16:09,840 --> 00:16:12,040
 So, people are getting interested.

108
00:16:12,040 --> 00:16:26,040
 So, until that, we are so blessed because there are some priests, sisters, lay families, that they have these relics of saints, and they believe in our mission.

109
00:16:26,040 --> 00:16:30,540
 So, they gave it to us, they donated it to us from America, from Europe.

110
00:16:30,540 --> 00:16:38,740
 So, we made this tour of sacred relics, wherein we go around the whole Philippines for free, for free.

111
00:16:38,740 --> 00:16:42,740
 So, when we do this, we also bring Blessed Ivan.

112
00:16:42,740 --> 00:16:46,740
 So, that is our way of promoting Blessed Ivan Merce.

113
00:16:46,740 --> 00:16:57,940
 And not only in terms of just putting the relic or putting the image or giving away, we also give cateches, we also give, you know, seminars.

114
00:16:57,940 --> 00:17:03,940
 And at the same time, we give images of Blessed Ivan in churches.

115
00:17:03,940 --> 00:17:11,140
 But still, we said, "This is something, you know, we need to, we need more.

116
00:17:11,140 --> 00:17:13,140
 We need something new."

117
00:17:13,140 --> 00:17:19,140
 Because these are already, you know, sometimes we call it, you know, "gasgasna," or it's very traditional.

118
00:17:19,140 --> 00:17:20,140
 Let's do something.

119
00:17:20,140 --> 00:17:45,340
 So, we go to another mission, and these are the missions of sanctification, the missions of evangelization, the mission of charity, wherein we are not only limited in the walls of the church, but also we make the streets as our church, as our venue of promoting Blessed Ivan.

120
00:17:45,340 --> 00:17:52,540
 And you spoke about all these missions that you do, sanctification, evangelization, charity.

121
00:17:52,540 --> 00:17:55,540
 How did you start with that?

122
00:17:55,540 --> 00:18:01,140
 What was the first cause of you starting the center itself?

123
00:18:01,140 --> 00:18:10,540
 You said you prayed for it a long time, but what was the vision and what was the fire that kept you going in those difficult times?

124
00:18:10,540 --> 00:18:17,740
 So, since 2003, we are already doing this tour of sacred relics and promoting Blessed Ivan.

125
00:18:17,740 --> 00:18:25,740
 So, many people are asking, "Where can we now visit these relics if you do not have any tour?"

126
00:18:25,740 --> 00:18:35,740
 So, just imagine, we go to malls, we go to churches, we go to even government structures, establishments.

127
00:18:35,740 --> 00:18:41,940
 And they will all say, "We want to visit these relics, even if you do not have any tours."

128
00:18:41,940 --> 00:18:48,940
 So, in 2017, we decided to build the first Blessed Ivan Center in Quezon City.

129
00:18:48,940 --> 00:18:52,940
 But because we were flooded that time, you just imagine, 20 feet flood.

130
00:18:52,940 --> 00:18:59,140
 So, we said that you need to transfer.

131
00:18:59,140 --> 00:19:07,140
 And right now, we transferred in 2018 in Marikina City, that is in the east of Manila.

132
00:19:07,140 --> 00:19:10,140
 And that is the cleanest city in the whole Philippines.

133
00:19:10,140 --> 00:19:13,140
 So, we're very proud to say that.

134
00:19:13,140 --> 00:19:21,340
 And we built this small chapel, started with the oratory, a small room like this one or maybe half of this.

135
00:19:21,340 --> 00:19:27,340
 And then after a year, we renovated it, we repaired it until it became a chapel.

136
00:19:27,340 --> 00:19:34,540
 Now, the chapel itself became an oasis, a center for devotees.

137
00:19:34,540 --> 00:19:42,540
 It's a center for those who are already volunteering for Blessed Ivan and those who are interested to get to know him more.

138
00:19:42,540 --> 00:19:48,740
 And we said that this center will be nothing if there will be no action.

139
00:19:48,740 --> 00:20:06,740
 So, we decided in 2018 as a new religious corporation recognized by the Philippine government to organize and to make it more clear our purpose here in the Philippines and also in the world.

140
00:20:06,740 --> 00:20:16,940
 So, we divided the three missions that we have seen in the life of Blessed Ivan: sanctification, evangelization, and charity.

141
00:20:16,940 --> 00:20:22,940
 So, let me start with the charity because the charity is the longest.

142
00:20:22,940 --> 00:20:26,940
 We were established in 2003.

143
00:20:26,940 --> 00:20:33,940
 The charity mission started in 2003 also with the Blessed Ivan Scholarship Fund.

144
00:20:33,940 --> 00:20:41,140
 We gather, you know, young people, poor young people, but deserving young people, to bring them to school.

145
00:20:41,140 --> 00:20:43,140
 We pay everything.

146
00:20:43,140 --> 00:20:47,540
 And we also give them formation of the Catholic faith.

147
00:20:47,540 --> 00:20:51,140
 And believe it or not, we already have engineers.

148
00:20:51,140 --> 00:20:54,540
 We already have librarians, teachers.

149
00:20:54,540 --> 00:21:11,740
 And right now, our scholars, we have four scholars right now, and one of them is the most smartest young man in one city, in Pasig City.

150
00:21:11,740 --> 00:21:17,740
 Historically, he got a perfect average, 99%.

151
00:21:17,740 --> 00:21:24,940
 Meaning, maybe he's like Einstein, and he's one of our scholars, but he's very Catholic.

152
00:21:24,940 --> 00:21:31,940
 And the Scholarship Fund helps us in forming more leaders for the church.

153
00:21:31,940 --> 00:21:34,940
 And then the second is our feeding program.

154
00:21:34,940 --> 00:21:41,940
 We go to the streets feeding the homeless because, you know, Philippines, the poverty is so high.

155
00:21:41,940 --> 00:21:46,140
 So many are, you know, staying in the streets.

156
00:21:46,140 --> 00:21:53,140
 So every month, we go out of the streets and give them a one-month supply of food.

157
00:21:53,140 --> 00:22:07,340
 And we get this from our donors, from the donations from the masses, and of course, from the partner schools that they donate food, vitamins, etc.

158
00:22:07,340 --> 00:22:13,340
 And then for the evangelization mission, we know that Blessed Evan Merce is a teacher.

159
00:22:13,340 --> 00:22:20,340
 So we said we need to, you know, follow the life of Blessed Evan Merce through education.

160
00:22:20,340 --> 00:22:24,540
 So we build first the Path Fire Philippines.

161
00:22:24,540 --> 00:22:35,540
 This is the mission wherein we give retreats, recollections, seminars to public schools and non-Catholic institutions for free.

162
00:22:35,540 --> 00:22:38,540
 So we help them in their formation.

163
00:22:38,540 --> 00:22:40,540
 We help them in their human formation.

164
00:22:40,540 --> 00:22:47,740
 And the second one is the mission of evangelization, the Merce Institute.

165
00:22:47,740 --> 00:22:59,740
 This is our newest mission, two years old, that we offer online courses offering theology, philosophy, and liturgy for free.

166
00:22:59,740 --> 00:23:02,940
 So we teach them, you know, through online.

167
00:23:02,940 --> 00:23:11,940
 And we are very happy that we already have two graduations with more than 30 graduates, you know, of this Merce Institute.

168
00:23:11,940 --> 00:23:13,140
 Wow, beautiful.

169
00:23:13,140 --> 00:23:26,140
 And what's the feedback, especially with the public schools and non-Catholic schools receiving formation from somebody who is promoting a saint?

170
00:23:26,140 --> 00:23:27,140
 Yeah.

171
00:23:27,140 --> 00:23:33,140
 Well, to be honest, they were all surprised that, you know, someone giving it for free.

172
00:23:33,140 --> 00:23:34,140
 Yes.

173
00:23:34,140 --> 00:23:35,140
 No?

174
00:23:35,140 --> 00:23:37,340
 Well, that's how it works.

175
00:23:37,340 --> 00:23:38,340
 We offer it for free.

176
00:23:38,340 --> 00:23:47,340
 And we do not only offer it for free, it has good quality, high-quality formation, high-quality Catholic formation.

177
00:23:47,340 --> 00:24:11,540
 And the teachers, the principal of the schools are so happy to receive such wonderful Christian formation from the blessed Evan Merce family, especially that right now, the government has already removed, you know, the permission of teaching catechism in the public schools out of, you know, the separation of church and state.

178
00:24:11,540 --> 00:24:25,540
 But here we are because of this, you know, teachers, principals who are devotees also blessed even, they became, you know, the key for us to do this mission in their institution.

179
00:24:25,540 --> 00:24:32,540
 And how long does the mission in a particular school last? How do you do it? What are the teachings?

180
00:24:32,540 --> 00:24:39,540
 So, normally, a recollection will happen for a day, but the retreat is around two or three days.

181
00:24:39,540 --> 00:24:47,540
 So, just like now, December 8th, we have two schools that are being given right now, retreats, no?

182
00:24:47,540 --> 00:25:05,540
 So, I'm very happy that this mission of formation in an informal way, because it's a retreat, recollection, still being embraced by many, even if they're not anywhere in the Catholic lining, no?

183
00:25:05,540 --> 00:25:09,540
 Of giving this wonderful formation.

184
00:25:09,540 --> 00:25:18,540
 Yeah, that's beautiful. You are touching the young that are going to be the future leaders of Philippines and maybe the world.

185
00:25:18,540 --> 00:25:19,540
 I agree.

186
00:25:19,540 --> 00:25:31,540
 And Merce Institute, when did you found it? How did it all started? Do you teach by yourself or you have somebody else that is also included in the process?

187
00:25:31,540 --> 00:25:42,540
 Yeah. So, the Merce Institute started two years ago. I can still remember November 1. First, we offer the course on hagiography about the saints.

188
00:25:42,540 --> 00:25:55,540
 And then, we offer liturgy, philosophy, and theology. And I'm very happy that some of my friends who are also professors of philosophy and theology are helping the Merce Institute.

189
00:25:55,540 --> 00:26:06,540
 And it started because during the pandemic, we said we need to do something for feeding the minds and the souls of our Catholic faithful.

190
00:26:06,540 --> 00:26:19,540
 And our target in this institute are the active members already in the church, like altar servers, lectors, or maybe lay leaders of the church,

191
00:26:19,540 --> 00:26:33,540
 who would like to receive Catholic education in a quality, maybe affordable also because we ask, you know, minimal donation of just 51 euro for the whole course.

192
00:26:33,540 --> 00:26:38,540
 And because we are now in the jubilee year of Blessed Evangelion, we offer it for free.

193
00:26:38,540 --> 00:26:54,540
 And they are all surprised that the Merce Institute offers, you know, very conservative Catholic doctrine, but in a pastoral and contextual way of explaining the Catholic doctrine.

194
00:26:54,540 --> 00:27:19,540
 That's why they are very welcoming in this kind of mission that we offer this institute, you know, because, you know, in the Philippines, we have so many institutes that, you know, they're very, you know, expensive or sometimes we cannot understand them, you know, even Jesus Christ will be very difficult to understand himself if someone is, you know, attending this institute.

195
00:27:19,540 --> 00:27:28,540
 But what we do is we put our shoes on the Church of Blessed Evangelion which is teaching young people.

196
00:27:28,540 --> 00:27:48,540
 That's why we always look at it, even there are already priests or sisters, we look at them as young people so that our method of teaching will be more, you know, dialogue, conversational, and at the same time, our way of offering this.

197
00:27:48,540 --> 00:27:53,540
 And this course is very sound doctrine.

198
00:27:53,540 --> 00:28:00,540
 And that is what we need in the Philippines right now because of, you know, too much social media, too much this and that.

199
00:28:00,540 --> 00:28:13,540
 So now the Merce Institute will offer them this pure and quality Catholic education through an online platform.

200
00:28:13,540 --> 00:28:15,540
 And do you ever meet with them in person?

201
00:28:15,540 --> 00:28:28,540
 Yes, we meet them especially during their graduation, you know, so we're very happy that we already have two graduation and some of them are from the sisters and some priests who are attending our courses.

202
00:28:28,540 --> 00:28:29,540
 Yeah, that's great.

203
00:28:29,540 --> 00:28:30,540
 Yeah, that's great.

204
00:28:30,540 --> 00:28:36,540
 And besides charity and evangelization, one of your missions is sanctification.

205
00:28:36,540 --> 00:28:37,540
 Yes.

206
00:28:37,540 --> 00:28:38,540
 How do you do it?

207
00:28:38,540 --> 00:28:47,540
 How do you bring people to a closer intimacy with God and so that they can sanctify themselves, make themselves become saints?

208
00:28:47,540 --> 00:28:48,540
 Yes, yes.

209
00:28:48,540 --> 00:29:02,540
 You know, this mission of sanctification is rooted in the words of Blessed Ivan, that the purpose of man is to become a saint and to incarnate Jesus Christ.

210
00:29:02,540 --> 00:29:19,540
 And I mentioned before that we have this tour of sacred relics that through the relics of the saints, we do not only offer them, you know, an encounter with the saints, but also for them to, you know, to see that, oh, saints are real people.

211
00:29:19,540 --> 00:29:24,540
 Saints are like us, sinners, but also there is striving to be holy.

212
00:29:24,540 --> 00:29:30,540
 So the first one is the tour of sacred relics that wherein we bring the relics of the saints for free.

213
00:29:30,540 --> 00:29:35,540
 Then we give them, you know, we celebrate holy mass, we give them cateches.

214
00:29:35,540 --> 00:29:56,540
 And of course, if the parish priest or the bishop will allow us to do healing masses wherein we use the healing oil of Blessed Ivan, excuse me, when we use the oil of Blessed Ivan, we use this through the priest will bless and exercise it.

215
00:29:56,540 --> 00:30:03,540
 Then we will dip the bone of Blessed Ivan in that oil and then we use it for healing.

216
00:30:03,540 --> 00:30:08,540
 And then the second sanctification mission is the reliquarium.

217
00:30:08,540 --> 00:30:10,540
 This is the center of Blessed Ivan.

218
00:30:10,540 --> 00:30:16,540
 And the chapel is called reliquarium because it is the house for the sacred relics.

219
00:30:16,540 --> 00:30:26,540
 And that is the house of the relic of Blessed Ivan, the image of Blessed Ivan, and the first image outside Croatia in Asia of Maria Bistritsa.

220
00:30:26,540 --> 00:30:30,540
 So we're bringing, you know, Croatia in the Philippines.

221
00:30:30,540 --> 00:30:34,540
 So there's a little bit of a side story.

222
00:30:34,540 --> 00:30:43,540
 One time there are some people in the Philippines went to our chapel and they thought that it was the embassy of Croatia.

223
00:30:43,540 --> 00:30:46,540
 Because we have the flag of Croatia outside.

224
00:30:46,540 --> 00:30:51,540
 So I said, we need to bring it down because you're not the embassy of the Philippines, of Croatia in the Philippines.

225
00:30:51,540 --> 00:30:54,540
 Anyway, so the chapel is called reliquarium.

226
00:30:54,540 --> 00:30:56,540
 So Maria Bistritsa is there.

227
00:30:56,540 --> 00:30:58,540
 The sacred heart of Zagreb is there.

228
00:30:58,540 --> 00:31:09,540
 So it's like bringing Croatia to the Philippines as our, you know, our way of showing the beauty of the Catholic faith of the Croats.

229
00:31:09,540 --> 00:31:17,540
 Now, in that reliquarium, so it houses the relics of the saints, which we bring in the Torah sacred relics.

230
00:31:17,540 --> 00:31:23,540
 And then these were donated by people who are really believing in our mission.

231
00:31:23,540 --> 00:31:33,540
 And people there that do not only, you know, see the relics, but also they pray and ask Blessed Evans' intercession for healing.

232
00:31:33,540 --> 00:31:40,540
 And the way that we do that is every Sunday, we have celebration of the Mass, of the Holy Mass.

233
00:31:40,540 --> 00:31:48,540
 And only in Marikina that the chapel offers regular confession, 30 minutes before the Mass.

234
00:31:48,540 --> 00:31:58,540
 And many people really flock in our chapel to go to confession because the priests are, you know, very engaged of doing the sacrament.

235
00:31:58,540 --> 00:32:07,540
 And at the same time, every first Sunday of the month, we have this healing masses wherein people come to our chapel.

236
00:32:07,540 --> 00:32:10,540
 They are given the sacrament of the anointing of the sick.

237
00:32:10,540 --> 00:32:21,540
 And after that, some healing priests in our country, they also visit the chapel to do their special healing ministry with the oil of Blessed Evans.

238
00:32:21,540 --> 00:32:33,540
 And also in that chapel, we are very blessed that because many priests believe in the authenticity of these relics,

239
00:32:33,540 --> 00:32:42,540
 and at the same time we had the blessed sacrament, some priests would like to use the chapel as a center for deliverance and exorcism.

240
00:32:42,540 --> 00:32:47,540
 And our spiritual, one of our spiritual director is an exorcist.

241
00:32:47,540 --> 00:32:56,540
 So people flock there asking the intercessor of Blessed Evans for their deliverance, especially of young people.

242
00:32:56,540 --> 00:33:08,540
 Automatically, if someone is, you know, in his young age, who is either possessed, obsessed, or oppressed, automatically priests in the Philippines or some of our friends go to the reliquium.

243
00:33:08,540 --> 00:33:09,540
 Go to Blessed Evans.

244
00:33:09,540 --> 00:33:10,540
 He will help you.

245
00:33:10,540 --> 00:33:17,540
 And believe it or not, I already witnessed two or three exorcisms, and it's very fast.

246
00:33:17,540 --> 00:33:26,540
 Meaning, Blessed Evans is very effective, powerful intercessor when it comes to healing and deliverance.

247
00:33:26,540 --> 00:33:30,540
 So the power of intercession is strong.

248
00:33:30,540 --> 00:33:38,540
 Do you have any specific testimony that you can share with us about healing or deliverance from somebody from the youth?

249
00:33:38,540 --> 00:33:39,540
 Yeah.

250
00:33:39,540 --> 00:33:44,540
 I remember one time that, anyway, this is not any more confidential. I will not mention the name.

251
00:33:44,540 --> 00:34:03,540
 One girl was brought to us because her parents, oh my God, I'm a little bit emotional, saw her hanging herself in her room.

252
00:34:03,540 --> 00:34:14,540
 And they know that that is not her because they're very Catholic. They're a Catholic family. The girl is studying in the Catholic school.

253
00:34:14,540 --> 00:34:26,540
 But one time they realized that the girl has changed behaviorally, you know, in her absence.

254
00:34:26,540 --> 00:34:44,540
 So until in the school, it was the religion teacher, the catechism teacher who endorsed that girl to us and asked that the family can bring it to the reliquium and said, "Okay."

255
00:34:44,540 --> 00:34:55,540
 So here comes the girl, and we saw her, all the wounds in her palm, in her arms.

256
00:34:55,540 --> 00:35:05,540
 And our exorcist priest just looked at her, and the girl looked at her, and looked at Blessed Ivan.

257
00:35:05,540 --> 00:35:15,540
 And I don't know what language she said. But she was pointing to Blessed Ivan. Blah, blah, blah, blah, blah.

258
00:35:15,540 --> 00:35:30,540
 And during the, it was only right now, during my visit, in the part of the Our Father in Croatia, the lead us, deliver us from evil. The evil in Croatia is?

259
00:35:30,540 --> 00:35:31,540
 Zlok.

260
00:35:31,540 --> 00:35:32,540
 Zlok.

261
00:35:32,540 --> 00:35:33,540
 Zlok.

262
00:35:33,540 --> 00:35:48,540
 Yeah. It was only zlok. So he was, he was repeating. And the priest, you know, she prayed over, do the exorcism rite, etc., and brought out the relic of Blessed Ivan.

263
00:35:48,540 --> 00:36:01,540
 And in Latin, the girl said, I hate this man. He brought many souls to heaven. And she is pointing to Blessed Ivan.

264
00:36:01,540 --> 00:36:16,540
 So that is my, I can say, one of the best experience and encounter of how this, you know, this possess, you know, testify how Blessed Ivan is very hot.

265
00:36:16,540 --> 00:36:27,540
 How Blessed Ivan is very holy. Of course, in the Philippines, we cannot tell that because, or as many will come to the Philippines. I'm telling it now because no one can go to the Philippines.

266
00:36:27,540 --> 00:36:42,540
 But just imagine that young girl. And for me, that experience really affirmed to me that Blessed Ivan really is a saint.

267
00:36:42,540 --> 00:36:43,540
 Yes.

268
00:36:43,540 --> 00:37:01,540
 That's why automatically, many schools, many priests who are asking relic of Blessed Ivan, we will always tell them, Father, use this if there's young people being, you know, possessed or whatever, spiritual warfare that they're encountering.

269
00:37:01,540 --> 00:37:09,540
 Please use Blessed Ivan. And I can tell you, many can testify that Blessed Ivan is so powerful before God.

270
00:37:09,540 --> 00:37:32,540
 Yes. I believe the same. We had a lot of testimonies of people who came to us that Ivan really helped. And what really touched me while you were speaking, besides the testimony that is very emotional, is that you really cherish the Croatian heritage of the catalysis and what we have.

271
00:37:32,540 --> 00:37:54,540
 Can you, most of the people who will watch this interview are the youth from Croatia. Also those that moved outside Croatia because of work and because of family. Can you share a message to them about the beauty of Croatian spiritual heritage?

272
00:37:54,540 --> 00:38:08,540
 Yeah. First of all, I would like to thank you for giving Blessed Ivan Mirs, sharing him not only to me, but to all the Filipino Catholics.

273
00:38:08,540 --> 00:38:18,540
 Blessed Ivan is truly a gift from Croatia, by Croatians, not only for Croatia, but for the whole world.

274
00:38:18,540 --> 00:38:37,540
 And if only many people will work together promoting Blessed Ivan Mirs and offering it to the world, I can say that we can really change the young people, especially those who are encountering depressions, mental health issues, spiritual issues.

275
00:38:37,540 --> 00:38:44,540
 I'm sure that Blessed Ivan Mirs would like to embrace each one of us.

276
00:38:44,540 --> 00:39:01,540
 And I can say that if we are doing our part in promoting Blessed Ivan, please also help and have this desire to promote him, not only to your family, but to your friends, in your school, in your classmates.

277
00:39:01,540 --> 00:39:11,540
 We are so blessed to have this young man from Croatia who is inspiring young Filipinos, Filipino Catholics.

278
00:39:11,540 --> 00:39:29,540
 And if Blessed Ivan became a sign of our unity and a familial community, I'm sure that he will also strengthen your family, your community, if you will ask his intercession.

279
00:39:29,540 --> 00:39:33,540
 Blessed Ivan Mirs is so powerful to God.

280
00:39:33,540 --> 00:39:37,540
 We call him the powerful and compassionate intercessor.

281
00:39:37,540 --> 00:39:46,540
 We always tell that in the Philippines because he's not only praying for us, he's compassionate because he knows what we're undergoing through.

282
00:39:46,540 --> 00:39:50,540
 Especially I myself underwent depression.

283
00:39:50,540 --> 00:39:54,540
 I myself underwent anxiety, mental health issues.

284
00:39:54,540 --> 00:40:01,540
 But Blessed Ivan Mirs was there telling me, you know, I undergo through this also.

285
00:40:01,540 --> 00:40:03,540
 I was hated by many.

286
00:40:03,540 --> 00:40:05,540
 I was not accepted by many.

287
00:40:05,540 --> 00:40:06,540
 But still I'm here.

288
00:40:06,540 --> 00:40:07,540
 I'm standing.

289
00:40:07,540 --> 00:40:09,540
 So what does it mean?

290
00:40:09,540 --> 00:40:13,540
 We have someone who can understand us.

291
00:40:13,540 --> 00:40:15,540
 We have someone who could help us.

292
00:40:15,540 --> 00:40:17,540
 We have someone who will pray for us.

293
00:40:17,540 --> 00:40:18,540
 Who will journey with us.

294
00:40:18,540 --> 00:40:20,540
 And that is Blessed Ivan Mirs.

295
00:40:20,540 --> 00:40:31,540
 That's why if we are blessed to have Blessed Ivan Mirs, I'm sure that you are more blessed because you are here with him in Zagreb.

296
00:40:31,540 --> 00:40:32,540
 You can visit him anytime.

297
00:40:32,540 --> 00:40:36,540
 We just have, you know, we just have a small bone of Blessed Ivan.

298
00:40:36,540 --> 00:40:39,540
 But you have here the whole body of Blessed Ivan.

299
00:40:39,540 --> 00:40:46,540
 If we are blessed already with that tangible sign of Blessed Ivan, I'm sure that you are more blessed.

300
00:40:46,540 --> 00:40:54,540
 That's why please take this opportunity of having this wonderful relationship with Blessed Ivan Mirs.

301
00:40:54,540 --> 00:41:01,540
 I tell you, he will not regret a friendship that you want to build with him.

302
00:41:01,540 --> 00:41:05,540
 So please pray to Blessed Ivan as his intercession.

303
00:41:05,540 --> 00:41:11,540
 And I am sure he will lead you to Jesus, especially to his sacred heart.

304
00:41:11,540 --> 00:41:14,540
 The heart that is full of love.

305
00:41:14,540 --> 00:41:15,540
 Thank you, Dave.

306
00:41:15,540 --> 00:41:16,540
 Thank you.

307
00:41:16,540 --> 00:41:19,540
 Thank you very much for this beautiful message.

308
00:41:19,540 --> 00:41:23,540
 Just for the ending, we don't have a lot more time.

309
00:41:23,540 --> 00:41:29,540
 Can you tell us what are the future plans for the center of Ivan Mirs in the Philippines?

310
00:41:29,540 --> 00:41:30,540
 Yeah.

311
00:41:30,540 --> 00:41:33,540
 So right now we are celebrating the year of Thanksgiving.

312
00:41:33,540 --> 00:41:35,540
 It's our 20th anniversary.

313
00:41:35,540 --> 00:41:46,540
 So five years from now, we are planning to build a bigger chapel of Blessed Ivan Mirs where we can at least accommodate 500 people.

314
00:41:46,540 --> 00:41:47,540
 and then we have the school of MERS Institute.

315
00:41:47,540 --> 00:42:00,540
 We will also have the columbary for the urn that will be specialized for the poor people who die on the streets.

316
00:42:00,540 --> 00:42:07,540
 And then we also have this 24 hours open adoration chapel drive-thru.

317
00:42:07,540 --> 00:42:16,540
 just like McDonald's drive-thru so that the busy people of Metro Manila can still meet Jesus in the Blessed Sacrament.

318
00:42:16,540 --> 00:42:30,540
 So that is the first plan of a bigger chapel, a bigger reliquarium as we are told, because we want to make this center not only for the few, but for many, but for all.

319
00:42:30,540 --> 00:42:36,540
 So I hope that you pray for us so that this will happen.

320
00:42:36,540 --> 00:42:43,540
 And then second is hopefully someday as the family of Blessed Ivan Mirs in the Philippines goes bigger.

321
00:42:43,540 --> 00:42:58,540
 We hope to have this, our own congregation of priests and brothers dedicated in the promotion of Blessed Ivan Mirs and continuing his legacy in the Philippines and also here in Croatia.

322
00:42:58,540 --> 00:42:59,540
 Thank you.

323
00:42:59,540 --> 00:43:00,540
 Thank you.

324
00:43:00,540 --> 00:43:01,540
 Thank you.

325
00:43:01,540 --> 00:43:03,540
 We will pray for you and you pray for us.

326
00:43:03,540 --> 00:43:04,540
 Thank you.

327
00:43:04,540 --> 00:43:10,540
 Thank you very much for this interview and I hope your work is going to be blessed by our Lord.

328
00:43:10,540 --> 00:43:11,540
 Thank you very much.

329
00:43:11,540 --> 00:43:12,540
 Thank you very much.

